Enforced the singleton policy for facade content types (`Vereadores`, `Normas`, `Legislaturas`, `Mesas`, `Comissoes`, `Materias`, `Sessoes`): once an instance exists at the portal, its `Add` permission is stripped so the type disappears from the "Add new" menu, and `IObjectWillBeAddedEvent` blocks any further attempt to create or copy/paste a second instance. A targeted patch to `_verifyObjectPaste` (OFS + `PasteBehaviourMixin`) keeps move and rename of the existing instance working. @ericof
